Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Chop @baby lettuce{1} into bite-size pieces. Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @Caesar dressing{1.5%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, 1⁄2 tsp Italian seasoning, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil, 1 tsp Italian seasoning, and a big squeeze of lemon juice. Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning—we sent more!

In a #large bowl{}, combine lettuce and half the creamy Caesar dressing; toss to coat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Spread remaining creamy Caesar dressing across bottom third of each tortilla. Top with chicken, tomato, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and as much salad as you like (be sure to reserve some salad for serving!).

Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide wraps and remaining salad between plates. Garnish salad with remaining Parmesan and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.